Package: amapR
Type: Package
Title: An R package using AMap API to convert addresses into coordinates
Version: 0.2.0
Author: Xiaojun Lin <linxiaojun@scu.edu.cn>
Maintainer: Xiaojun Lin <linxiaojun@scu.edu.cn>
Description: This R package provides useful tools for research using AMap Web Service API. 'amapR' currently can be use to convert Chinese addresses into coordinates. Benefiting from the parallel computing, this package has speed advantage in handeling huge data of addresses or coordinates. Theoratically, the more CPU cores you have, the faster the functions in this package will be. But please note that the Amap Web Service API have set the query limit (e.g., the upper query limits for personal certified developer are 200 times per second and 3 millions per day). 
URL: https://github.com/xiaojunlin/amapR
BugReports: https://github.com/xiaojunlin/amapR/issues
Imports: data.table, jsonlite, progress, parallel, doSNOW, foreach, stringr, stats, utils
NeedsCompilation: no
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
